ait, and has also performed written works at The Maidan Center at Dar Al Athar Al Islamiyya in Kuwait, and at The Mosaic Rooms in London. His interests include researching architectural trends in large institutional buildings, including schools and mosques. ',NULL),(39,1,'2014-05-06 20:55:55','2014-05-06 20:55:55',5,'Maysaa Almumin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Maysaa Almumin (b.1973) practiced architecture as a partner and co-founder of Small Architecture, sm architecture and Architects Independent, in both London, Kuwait, and Qatar. She is currently an Assistant Professor in the Department of Interior Design at Virginia Commonwealth University, Qatar and had also taught in the Department of Architecture at Kuwait University. She has exhibited and presented her exploratory projects as well as completed work, ranging from product and furniture design to architecture at nous gallery and Asia House, London, La Fontaine, Bahrain, Dar Al Funoon and Kuwait University, Kuwait and Katara Art Centre, Qatar. She graduated at Masters level from the Architectural Association School of Architecture, London.\r\n',NULL),(40,1,'2014-05-06 20:57:26','2014-05-06 20:57:26',6,'Aisha Alsager',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Aisha Alsager (b. 1983) is an architect, designer, and researcher with a preoccupation in material investigation and methods of making. She earned a B.Arch from Kuwait University and a Masters in Advanced Architectural Design from the Graduate School of Architecture, Planning, and Preservation at Columbia University. She received the Kinne Fellows Traveling Prize to research specialised hospital design in Northern Europe, and the Lucille Smyser Lownfish Memorial Prize for the best design problem in a graduate studio. Alsager has worked in Kuwait, Boston, and New York where her experience has ranged from web design, digital fabrication, material research, and temporary installations, to interiors, building, and urban design projects. \r\n',NULL),(41,1,'2014-05-06 20:59:42','2014-05-06 21:19:49',7,'Noura Alsager',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Noura Alsager (b. 1989) is a writer, editor, and researcher. Published in <i>Jadaliyya</i> and <i>Ibraaz</i>, her interests include contemporary fiction and poetry, as well as literary theory. In 2011, she was selected as one of the finalists for the Robert Fitzgerald Prize for Translation. She earned a BA in English from Boston University in 2012. ',NULL),(42,1,'2014-05-06 21:00:38','2014-05-06 21:00:38',8,'Fatima Alqabandi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','An architect at the NCCAL, Alqabandi (b. 1982) is a Team Leader at the Heritage and Restoration Dept., where she works the Al-Ahmadi Souq Project and Al-Ghanim Palace. She earned a B.Arch from Kuwait University in 2005, and in 2010, received the Dame Violet Dickson Scholarship from the UK’s Foreign and Commonwealth Office to fund her graduate degree from the Bartlett School of Architecture at UCL. Her Masters thesis focused on social sustainability in Middle Eastern cities. Her interests include travelling, art, and culture. \r\n',NULL),(43,1,'2014-05-06 21:01:17','2014-05-06 21:22:13',9,'Liane Al-Ghusain',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Liane Al-Ghusain (b. 1987) is a writer and teacher. From 2012 to 2013, she participated in Ashkal Alwan’s post-graduate Home Workspace Program in Beirut, Lebanon, where she studied art, technology, and performance. From 2011 to 2012, she directed the non-profit Contemporary Art Platform Kuwait. Al-Ghusain has contributed to publications such as <i>Bazaar</i>, <i>Al-Ostoura Magazine</i>, <i>Portal 9 Journal</i>, and <i>Nafas Art Magazine</i>. She completed a BA and MA in English Literature at Stanford University in 2010.',NULL),(44,1,'2014-05-06 21:01:56','2014-05-06 21:01:56',10,'Abdulla AlHarmi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Abdulla AlHarmi (b. 1989) works at the New Projects division at the National Council for Culture, Arts and Letters. Former board member of the Kuwait Architecture Student Association (KASA), he earned a B.Arch from Kuwait University. AlHarmi participated in KASA’s sixth and seventh annual exhibitions. ',NULL),(45,1,'2014-05-06 21:06:09','2014-05-06 21:25:39',11,'Dana Aljouder',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Dana Aljouder (b. 1986) is an interior designer and performance artist with a B.Arch from Pratt Institute. In 2008, she received the SILS Twining Fellowship to conduct research in Florence on allegories of the Medici family through Renaissance art. Also in 2008, she exhibited <i>The Chair</i> at the Pratt Institute’s Higgins Hall, and later in 2013 at <i>Kursi: A Tribute to a Chair</i> at the Design Terminal in Budapest. In 2010, she designed the Albert Reichmuth Wine Showroom in Zurich with OOS. In 2011, Aljouder collaborated with Bassem Mansour on <i>rwwzhyx- a controversy in sound</i> at Beirut Art Center’s <i>Exposures</i>, and they continue to perform in festivals such as <i>Altofest</i>. Currently, she works at Pace. ',NULL),(46,1,'2014-05-06 21:06:52','2014-05-06 21:06:52',12,'Wafaâ€™a Al-Fraheen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Wafa’a Al-Fraheen (b. 1973) worked at the Maidan Cultural Center for 11 years, and served as Surtitles Director and Company Manager of SABAB theatre. She\r\nstudied Aerospace Engineering at Manchester University and graduated with a Bachelor of Engineering in 1998. She completed additional studies in media and performance at Chester College. In 2001, she worked at various theatres in the Czech Republic.  \r\n',NULL),(47,1,'2014-05-06 21:10:01','2014-05-06 21:28:23',13,'Ghazi Al-Mulaifi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Ghazi Al-Mulaifi (b. 1977) is a musician, author, recording engineer, and ethnomusicologist. He is in the final phase of his candidacy for a PhD. in \r\nethnomusicology at New York University, where he was awarded a MacCraken Fellowship. His research interests include: Kuwaiti pearl diving music, corporeal transmissions of knowledge, and heritage production. In the spring of 2013, <i>Arte East Quarterly</i> published his article <i>All the Men Died at Sea</i>. Al-Mulaifi earned a B.A. in Philosophy with a Minor in Studio Composition from the State University of New York-Purchase College, and a Masters of Music from New York University.',NULL),(48,1,'2014-05-06 21:10:34','2014-05-06 21:10:34',14,'Noora Al Mussallam',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Noora Al Mussallam (b. 1990) received her B.Arch from Kuwait University in 2012, joined The Kuwait Fund Training Program, and interned at NADAAA in Boston for six months. Her interests include analyzing and reinterpreting information, finding and creating links in the research process, and creating a parallel line of thought between research and creativity.\r\n',NULL),(49,1,'2014-05-06 21:11:18','2014-05-06 21:11:18',15,'Nesef Al Nesef',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','With a BA in Architecture from Pratt Institute, Nesef Al Nesef (b. 1981) practices architecture as well as interior and retail design. Through the Kuwait Fund Training Program, Al Nesef interned at OOS in Zurich, Switzerland, where he worked on design and scenography of permanent installations at the Verkehrshaus der Schweiz Museum. He has won the Young Arab Architects award at the Venice Biennale and at the Institut du Monde Arabe, and has exhibited his work at both venues. \r\n',NULL),(50,1,'2014-05-06 21:11:53','2014-05-06 21:11:53',16,'Adel Al-Qattan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Adel Al-Qattan (b. 1984) graduated from the University of Technology in Sydney with a BA in Journalism, and has attained diplomas in Communications and Engineering from Insearch in Sydney. He is currently employed at the National Council for Culture, Arts and Letters, and has experience in the fields of architecture, finance, hospitality, and charity. His interests revolve around music and the performing arts. ',NULL),(51,1,'2014-05-06 21:12:36','2014-05-06 21:12:36',17,'Dalal Al-Sane',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','An associate at the investment banking department at NBK Capital, Al-Sane (b. 1984) served as treasurer for the project. She obtained her BA in Business Administration and Political Science from Washington University in 2006. Her interests include outdoor activities, reading, and writing. She has been a member of local book clubs for more than three years. In 2014, she completed a 3,000m climb of Jebel Shams, Oman. She contributes to local publications. ',NULL),(52,1,'2014-05-06 21:13:13','2014-05-06 21:13:13',18,'Hassan Hayat',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','With a B.Arch and M.Arch from Tulane University, Hassan Hayat (b. 1979) is a practicing architect interested in multidisciplinary and sustainable approaches towards development. In 2012, he contributed to the Thukhur initiative for entrepreneurship and corporate innovation in partnership with the Ministry of Planning and Development. ',NULL),(53,1,'2014-05-06 21:14:00','2014-05-06 21:14:00',19,'GrÃ¡inne Hebeler',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','A researcher and Arabic language student, Hebeler (b. 1987) focuses on the architectural evolution of Kuwait, from the formation of the State to the discovery of oil. Previously, Hebeler worked at the Phoebe A. Hearst Museum of Anthropology at the University of California in Berkeley, where she coordinated and aided in the relocation project of 1.7 million artefacts. Hebeler graduated from Bates College with degrees in the Classics and Anthropology in 2010. She received the Barlow Thesis Research Grant. ',NULL),(54,1,'2014-05-06 21:14:26','2014-05-06 21:14:26',20,'Samer Mohammed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Samer Mohammed (b. 1988) is interested in the fields of research, analysis, and diagrammatic representations of information. He enjoys seeing the way information assists in clarifying possibilities that lead to strong end results. He graduated with a B.Arch from Kuwait University. ',NULL),(55,1,'2014-05-06 21:15:18','2014-05-06 21:29:20',21,'Sara SaragoÃ§a Soares',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Sara Saragoça Soares (b. 1975) is an architect with a Masters in Preservation, Building Conservation and Urban Rehabilitation from the College of Architecture at Lisbon Technical University. At FAUTL, her research focused on preservation of modernist buildings in Kuwait. During her career in Portugal, Soares centered her practice on architectural rehabilitation projects. In 2012, she moved to Kuwait to work on the Al Shaheed Park Development Project for the Al Amiri Diwan. Also, she is a contributing researcher for an upcoming exhibition at Dar Al-Athar Al-Islamiyyah entitled, <i>Modernist Architecture in Kuwait</i>.',NULL),(56,1,'2014-05-09 19:00:10','2014-05-09 19:00:10',NULL,'Untitled',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(57,1,'2014-06-02 11:44:55','2014-06-02 12:09:02',2,'.Law of Antiquities 1960',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(58,1,'2014-06-02 12:00:59','2014-06-02 12:00:59',NULL,'.Soor Demolition Act 1957',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(59,1,'2014-06-02 12:18:39','2014-06-02 12:18:39',NULL,'.Malene Bjorn: The Light and Airy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,